      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "The Hendricks County Sheriff’s department just released details about the fatal crash that happened at noon today in Avon.\n\nAccording to multiple eyewitnesses a Freightliner semi-truck with trailer was traveling eastbound on US 36 when it ran the red light at the intersection of CR 525E and struck a northbound Chevrolet pickup truck.  \n\nThe impact caused the pickup to travel across the grass median where it hit a Chrysler Sebring that was stationary on westbound US 36 in the left turn lane. \n\nThe driver of the Chevrolet pickup truck, 64-year-old Terry Schultz, was pronounced dead at the scene.  \n\nCrash reconstruction specialists are still on the scene conducting the investigation and the intersection is partially closed at this time.￼",
      "text_resolved": "The Hendricks County Sheriff’s department just released details about the fatal crash that happened at noon today in Avon.\n\nAccording to multiple eyewitnesses a Freightliner semi-truck with trailer was traveling eastbound on US 36 when it ran the red light at the intersection of CR 525E and struck a northbound Chevrolet pickup truck.  \n\nThe impact caused the pickup to travel across the grass median where it hit a Chrysler Sebring that was stationary on westbound US 36 in the left turn lane. \n\nThe driver of the Chevrolet pickup truck, 64-year-old Terry Schultz, was pronounced dead at the scene.  \n\nCrash reconstruction specialists are still on the scene conducting the investigation and the intersection is partially closed at this time.￼",
